# Dashify Architecture

## Routing Split (Critical)

- `src/app/` — **App Router only**: pages and layouts. NO API routes here.
- `src/pages/api/` — **All API routes** (Pages Router). Never put API routes in `src/app/`.
- `src/pages/404.js` — Custom 404 page.

## Data Model

```
User → Dashboard (board) → Tile[]  (positioned content boxes)
                         → Pod[]   (container grouping Tiles)
```

- **Tile** has dual position: desktop (`x`, `y`, `width`, `height`) + mobile (`mobileX`, `mobileY`, `mobileWidth`, `mobileHeight`) + `order`
- **Pod** has its own position/size and contains Tile ObjectId refs
- Width/height values are stored as strings with `px` suffix (e.g. `"300px"`)
- All Mongoose models in `src/models/` use `models.X || model(...)` pattern to avoid re-registration

## State Management — Two Contexts

**Do not consolidate without understanding the dependency chain.**

| Context | File | Purpose |
|---------|------|---------|
| `globalContext` | `src/context/appContext.js` | Legacy: `dbUser`, `boards`, `tiles`, `activeBoard` — used by Header.js |
| `optimizedContext` | `src/context/optimizedContext.js` | React Query–backed board lists; `setBoards`/`setTiles`/`setActiveBoard` are deprecated no-ops |

- Both are mounted in `src/app/layout.js`
- Dashboard page reads from `optimizedContext` via `useDashboardData(id)`
- `setBoards`/`setTiles` on `optimizedContext` log warnings — use query invalidation instead

## React Query Patterns

- Query key factory: `dashboardKeys` in `src/hooks/useDashboard.js`
- Optimized axios instance: `optimizedAxios` from `src/hooks/useOptimizedQuery.js`
- Use `queryClient.invalidateQueries` / `queryClient.setQueryData` for cache updates
- Stale time: 2 min for user dashboards, 10 min for admin/guest dashboards

## Auth & Guest Mode

- Auth0 (`@auth0/nextjs-auth0`) for authentication
- Guests use `localStorage` key `"Dasify"` for board persistence
- Always use `safeSetItem`/`safeGetItem` from `src/utils/safeLocalStorage.js` for localStorage access
- On login, guest data migrates via `POST /api/manage/addGuestData`
- Admin-seeded boards (`hasAdminAdded: true` on Dashboard model) shown to guests

## API Route Conventions

- Connect to MongoDB via `src/lib/utils.js` (call `connectDB()` at top of each route)
- Return `{ error: message }` with proper HTTP status on failure
- Tile width/height always stored as strings: `"300px"` not `300`

## Mobile vs Desktop

- `useIsMobile` hook determines layout
- `GridTiles.js` (desktop) uses `react-rnd` for drag-and-resize
- `MobileGridTiles.js` (mobile) uses stacked layout sorted by `tile.order`
- Mobile tile width = `window.innerWidth - 48px` (24px margin each side)

## Import Alias

`@/*` → `src/*` (configured in `jsconfig.json`)
